    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "<del>Here's an api proposal for the Results/Query conditional display: \nWe could have a `Conditional` widget that will take a `show` prop. This prop will take a function with `(state, results)` as parameters and will expect a boolean in return. \nExample with the Query/NoQuery example: \n```js\n<Conditional show={(state, results) => !state.q}>\n      <div>No Query entered</div>\n</Conditional>\n<Conditional show={(state, results) => state.q}>\n      <div>a query is entered</div>\n</Conditional>\n```\nI voluntarily didn't include the `<HasItems>` one. Right now, with our current state management, I don't see an easy way to show again a facet after it has been hidden (either with clearAll button or by just uncheck other facets). \nWhat do you think ?\n</del>\n",
    "created_at": "2016-10-18T12:21:18Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1266#issuecomment-254490716",
